cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is about using reinforcement learning to train robot controllers for non-prehensile manipulation tasks, specifically pushing an object to various desired target positions. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as the focus is on controlling physical robots. The paper also discusses the use of simulation for training, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a modified form of the natural policy gradient algorithm for learning is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision for identifying the object and its position, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
